If you need to add header for the [SMTP protocol][3] there is a special input in the [SMTP sampler][4]:

[![enter image description here][5]][5]

Or if you prefer manually editing the XML:

	&lt;collectionProp name=&quot;SMTPSampler.headerFields&quot;&gt;
	  &lt;elementProp name=&quot;foo&quot; elementType=&quot;Argument&quot;&gt;
	    &lt;stringProp name=&quot;Argument.name&quot;&gt;foo&lt;/stringProp&gt;
	    &lt;stringProp name=&quot;Argument.value&quot;&gt;bar&lt;/stringProp&gt;
	  &lt;/elementProp&gt;
	&lt;/collectionProp&gt;


  [1]: https://www.blazemeter.com/blog/http-header-manager
  [2]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP
  [3]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simple_Mail_Transfer_Protocol
